repeaterAccessViolation.name: repeaterAccessViolation
repeaterAccessViolation.description: Controls action to take when an access violation occurs.

repeaterMyGroup.name: repeaterMyGroup
repeaterMyGroup.description: The index value of the group that is directly associated with the agent. The snmp support for the group associated with the agent is a superset of the support for other groups.

repeaterFifoOverflows.name: repeaterFifoOverflows
repeaterFifoOverflows.description: Deprecated, use repeaterRepeaterFifoOverflows in the repeaterRepeater group for the desired repeater.

repeaterLEDDisplay.name: repeaterLEDDisplay
repeaterLEDDisplay.description: Controls reason for flashing front panel LEDs.

repeaterReports.name: repeaterReports
repeaterReports.description: Deprecated, use repeaterRepeaterReports in the repeaterRepeater group for the desired repeater on which report generation is to be controlled.

repeaterHealthTrap.name: repeaterHealthTrap
repeaterHealthTrap.description: Controls the generation of the repeater health trap.

repeaterStatusChangeTrap.name: repeaterStatusChangeTrap
repeaterStatusChangeTrap.description: Controls the generation of the repeater status change trap.

repeaterAccessViolationTrap.name: repeaterAccessViolationTrap
repeaterAccessViolationTrap.description: Controls the generation of the repeater access violation trap.

repeaterIntegrityLossTrap.name: repeaterIntegrityLossTrap
repeaterIntegrityLossTrap.description: Controls the generation of the repeater integrity loss trap.

repeaterRedundancyPathChangeTrap.name: repeaterRedundancyPathChangeTrap
repeaterRedundancyPathChangeTrap.description: Controls the generation of the repeater redundancy path change trap.

repeaterGroupTable.name: repeaterGroupTable
repeaterGroupTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the groups.

repeaterGroupEntry.name: repeaterGroupEntry
repeaterGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a group.

repeaterGroupIndex.name: repeaterGroupIndex
repeaterGroupIndex.description: This variable identifies the group within the repeater for which this entry contains information. This value is the same as rptrGroupIndex.

repeaterGroupSQE.name: repeaterGroupSQE
repeaterGroupSQE.description: Deprecated, use repeaterRepeaterSQE in the repeaterRepeaterGroup for the SQE count on the desired repeater. This object will always return the count for repeater #1.

repeaterGroupJabbers.name: repeaterGroupJabbers
repeaterGroupJabbers.description: Deprecated, use repeaterRepeaterJabbers in the repeaterRepeaterGroup for the Jabber count on the desired repeater. This object will always return the count for repeater #1.

repeaterGroupSegment.name: repeaterGroupSegment
repeaterGroupSegment.description: Deprecated, use repeaterRepeaterSegment in the repeaterRepeaterGroup to control the segment mapping for the desired repeater. This object will always control the mapping for repeater #1.

repeaterGroupSecurityLock.name: repeaterGroupSecurityLock
repeaterGroupSecurityLock.description: This variable indicates the state of security lockdown on an unmanaged repeater. The only writable value is 'unlocked'.

repeaterGroupIOCardType.name: repeaterGroupIOCardType
repeaterGroupIOCardType.description: The hardware type of the I/O card, as defined in ITouch Assigned Numbers.

repeaterGroupIOCardFirmwareVersion.name: repeaterGroupIOCardFirmwareVersion
repeaterGroupIOCardFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the I/O card ROM.

repeaterGroupIOCardOperStatus.name: repeaterGroupIOCardOperStatus
repeaterGroupIOCardOperStatus.description: Relative to the chassis, the current operating status of the I/O card.

repeaterGroupManagement.name: repeaterGroupManagement
repeaterGroupManagement.description: This variable indicates the level of management control and observation available.

repeaterGroupRepeaterNumber.name: repeaterGroupRepeaterNumber
repeaterGroupRepeaterNumber.description: The number of logical repeaters visible via this repeater.

repeaterGroupRepeaterHardwareVersion.name: repeaterGroupRepeaterHardwareVersion
repeaterGroupRepeaterHardwareVersion.description: The repeater chip set hardware revision level.

repeaterGroupManagerRepeater.name: repeaterGroupManagerRepeater
repeaterGroupManagerRepeater.description: The logical repeater to which the manager card, if present, is attached.

repeaterGroupFifoErrors.name: repeaterGroupFifoErrors
repeaterGroupFifoErrors.description: This variable will reflect the number of times that the report FIFO has gone out of synchronization.

repeaterGroupCpuUtilization.name: repeaterGroupCpuUtilization
repeaterGroupCpuUtilization.description: The average CPU utilization for the processor which maintains statistics and implements monitoring for the group, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterGroupMemoryUtilization.name: repeaterGroupMemoryUtilization
repeaterGroupMemoryUtilization.description: The current memory utilization for the processor which maintains statistics and implements monitoring for the group, expressed as percentage used times 100.

repeaterGroupAlarmCount.name: repeaterGroupAlarmCount
repeaterGroupAlarmCount.description: The number of alarms currently being monitored by the processor for comparison with RMON thresholds.

repeaterPortTable.name: repeaterPortTable
repeaterPortTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the ports.

repeaterPortEntry.name: repeaterPortEntry
repeaterPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a port.

repeaterPortGroupIndex.name: repeaterPortGroupIndex
repeaterPortGroupIndex.description: This variable identifies the group containing the port for which this entry contains infromation.

repeaterPortIndex.name: repeaterPortIndex
repeaterPortIndex.description: This variable identifies the port within the group within the repeater for which this entry contains management information. This value can never be greater than rptrGroupPortCapacity for the associated group.

repeaterPortAutoPolarity.name: repeaterPortAutoPolarity
repeaterPortAutoPolarity.description: Controls whether the port will automatically determine its polarity.

repeaterPortPolarityDirection.name: repeaterPortPolarityDirection
repeaterPortPolarityDirection.description: If repeaterPortAutoPolarity is enabled, this is the current polarity of the port.

repeaterPortPulse.name: repeaterPortPulse
repeaterPortPulse.description: Controls whether the port will periodically generate a test pulse to determine the status of the port.

repeaterPortPulseStatus.name: repeaterPortPulseStatus
repeaterPortPulseStatus.description: If repeaterPortPulse is enabled, this is indicates whether the test pulse response is being detected.

repeaterPortPulseLosses.name: repeaterPortPulseLosses
repeaterPortPulseLosses.description: The number of times that a test pulse has been sent and a response was not received.

repeaterPortDistance.name: repeaterPortDistance
repeaterPortDistance.description: Controls whether the port will support extended distances on the port.

repeaterPortSofMissing.name: repeaterPortSofMissing
repeaterPortSofMissing.description: The number of times that alternating zero/one bits were seen after an inter-packet gap and were not followed by two one bits.

repeaterPortMCVs.name: repeaterPortMCVs
repeaterPortMCVs.description: The number of manchester violation errors detected on this port.

repeaterPortZero.name: repeaterPortZero
repeaterPortZero.description: Control to zero the hub port's counters. The agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect.

repeaterPortSinceZero.name: repeaterPortSinceZero
repeaterPortSinceZero.description: Number of time ticks since the port's counters were zeroed.

repeaterPortAccessAction.name: repeaterPortAccessAction
repeaterPortAccessAction.description: Control whether packets will be accepted or discarded if they are in the access list. The inverse action is applied to packets from all addresses not in the list.

repeaterPortAccessState.name: repeaterPortAccessState
repeaterPortAccessState.description: Indicates whether the port was disabled due to receiving a frame from an invalid source address.

repeaterPortAccessType.name: repeaterPortAccessType
repeaterPortAccessType.description: Indicates the type of the port.

repeaterPortAccessAllStatus.name: repeaterPortAccessAllStatus
repeaterPortAccessAllStatus.description: Setting this field to invalid will delete all access addresses associated with this port. Setting this field to valid has no effect.

repeaterPortPortLastViolationAddress.name: repeaterPortPortLastViolationAddress
repeaterPortPortLastViolationAddress.description: Address that last caused an access violation.

repeaterPortSegment.name: repeaterPortSegment
repeaterPortSegment.description: Returns the indirect mapping of the ethernet repeater to which this port is connected.

repeaterPortAccessLearn.name: repeaterPortAccessLearn
repeaterPortAccessLearn.description: Controls how the port will learn the source addresses that can come in on the port.

repeaterPortEthernetRepeater.name: repeaterPortEthernetRepeater
repeaterPortEthernetRepeater.description: For repeaters that implement non-proxy management of logical repeaters, this variable selects the logical Ethernet repeater to which the port is attached.

repeaterPortRepeatersAllowed.name: repeaterPortRepeatersAllowed
repeaterPortRepeatersAllowed.description: The list of repeaters to which this port can be attached. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with a bit for 'none' and one bit for each repeater, and enough octets for all the repeaters on the device. The high order bit of the first octet corresponds to 'none', the following bits correspond to the repeaters, in order, beginning with 1.

repeaterPortGlobalSecurityAddress.name: repeaterPortGlobalSecurityAddress
repeaterPortGlobalSecurityAddress.description: This variable represents the global address which is currently applied to the port.

repeaterPortGlobalAddressChanges.name: repeaterPortGlobalAddressChanges
repeaterPortGlobalAddressChanges.description: This variable represents the number of times since counters have been zeroed, that a global address change occured on the port.

repeaterPortPercentUtilization.name: repeaterPortPercentUtilization
repeaterPortPercentUtilization.description: This variable will reflect the percentage of a full ethernet load that this port has received since last zeroed. The value is calculated as '(8(bytesReceived + (20*framesReceived))) /107(time)'.

repeaterPortAccessTable.name: repeaterPortAccessTable
repeaterPortAccessTable.description: Table of access control for the ports.

repeaterPortAccessEntry.name: repeaterPortAccessEntry
repeaterPortAccessEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing access information about a port.

repeaterPortAccessGroupIndex.name: repeaterPortAccessGroupIndex
repeaterPortAccessGroupIndex.description: This variable identifies the group containing the access entry for which this entry contains information. The group ID may only be that of the target agent. Specifying a group ID of an agent in a different slot will result in `badValue` being returned.

repeaterPortAccessPortIndex.name: repeaterPortAccessPortIndex
repeaterPortAccessPortIndex.description: This variable identifies the port containing the access entry for which this entry contains information.

repeaterPortAccessAddress.name: repeaterPortAccessAddress
repeaterPortAccessAddress.description: This value will be compared to the source address of all packets received on the port in applying the access action

repeaterPortAccessStatus.name: repeaterPortAccessStatus
repeaterPortAccessStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the rule.

repeaterPortAccessGroupIndexShadow.name: repeaterPortAccessGroupIndexShadow
repeaterPortAccessGroupIndexShadow.description: This variable identifies the group which contains a port to which an access address is to be assigned. The group ID may only be that of the target agent. Specifying a group ID of an agent in a different slot will result in `badValue` being returned.

repeaterPortAccessPortIndexShadow.name: repeaterPortAccessPortIndexShadow
repeaterPortAccessPortIndexShadow.description: This variable identifies the port of a group to which an access address is to be assigned.

repeaterPortAccessAddressShadow.name: repeaterPortAccessAddressShadow
repeaterPortAccessAddressShadow.description: This value contains the ethernet address which is to be added to the access address table for the port specified by repeaterPortAccessGroupIndexShadow and repeaterPortAccessPortIndexShadow.

repeaterPortAccessStatusShadow.name: repeaterPortAccessStatusShadow
repeaterPortAccessStatusShadow.description: When read, this variable will always return 'ready'. When this variable is set to 'execute' the address specified by repeaterPortAccessAddressShadow will be added to the access address table for the port specified by repeaterPortAccessGroupIndexShadow and repeaterPortAccessPortIndexShadow. If any of the above variables are zero when this object is set to 'execute', 'bad value' will be returned.

repeaterPort2Table.name: repeaterPort2Table
repeaterPort2Table.description: Table of more descriptive and status information about the ports.

repeaterPort2Entry.name: repeaterPort2Entry
repeaterPort2Entry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a port. Index is identical to repeaterPortTable.

repeaterPort2RmonOctets.name: repeaterPort2RmonOctets
repeaterPort2RmonOctets.description: The total number of octets of data (including those in bad packets) received on the port (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts
repeaterPort2RmonPkts.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port.

repeaterPort2RmonBroadcastPkts.name: repeaterPort2RmonBroadcastPkts
repeaterPort2RmonBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of good packets received on the port that were directed to the broadcast address.

repeaterPort2RmonMulticastPkts.name: repeaterPort2RmonMulticastPkts
repeaterPort2RmonMulticastPkts.description: The total number of good packets received on the port that were directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

repeaterPort2RmonCRCAlignErrors.name: repeaterPort2RmonCRCAlignErrors
repeaterPort2RmonCRCAlignErrors.description: The total number of packets received on the port that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but were not an integral number of octets in length or had a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts64Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts64Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts64Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts65to127Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts65to127Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts65to127Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts128to255Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts128to255Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts128to255Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts256to511Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts256to511Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts256to511Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts512to1023Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts512to1023Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts512to1023Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2RmonPkts1024to1518Octets.name: repeaterPort2RmonPkts1024to1518Octets
repeaterPort2RmonPkts1024to1518Octets.description: The total number of packets (including error packets) received on the port that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

repeaterPort2TrafficRatio.name: repeaterPort2TrafficRatio
repeaterPort2TrafficRatio.description: The portion of segment bandwidth used by the port over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterPort2CollisionRatio.name: repeaterPort2CollisionRatio
repeaterPort2CollisionRatio.description: The ratio of collisions the port participated in to total packets over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterPort2ErrorRatio.name: repeaterPort2ErrorRatio
repeaterPort2ErrorRatio.description: The ratio of total number of error frames on the port to total packets over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterPort2BroadcastRatio.name: repeaterPort2BroadcastRatio
repeaterPort2BroadcastRatio.description: The ratio of good packets directed by the port to the broadcast address to total packets over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterPort2MulticastRatio.name: repeaterPort2MulticastRatio
repeaterPort2MulticastRatio.description: The ratio of good packets directed by the port to any multicast address (but not the broadcast address) to total packets over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterPort2UnicastRatio.name: repeaterPort2UnicastRatio
repeaterPort2UnicastRatio.description: The ratio of good packets directed by the port to any address other than a multicast or broadcast address to total packets over a 5 second interval, expressed as percentage times 100.

repeaterSecurityState.name: repeaterSecurityState
repeaterSecurityState.description: Controls whether security operation will be applied to all ports on the repeater. If security is not supported by the device, 'badValue' will be returned if the variable is set to 'enabled'.

repeaterSecurityPortTable.name: repeaterSecurityPortTable
repeaterSecurityPortTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the ports.

repeaterSecurityPortEntry.name: repeaterSecurityPortEntry
repeaterSecurityPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a port.

repeaterSecurityPortUnicast.name: repeaterSecurityPortUnicast
repeaterSecurityPortUnicast.description: The action to take when the destination address is unicast and does not have an entry in repeaterSecurityTable. If repeaterPortGroupIndex is equal to the group number of the agent, this object is read-write, otherwise it is read-only.

repeaterSecurityPortMulticast.name: repeaterSecurityPortMulticast
repeaterSecurityPortMulticast.description: The action to take when the destination address is multicast and does not have an entry in repeaterSecurityTable. If repeaterPortGroupIndex is equal to the group number of the agent, this object is read-write, otherwise it is read-only

repeaterSecurityPortAllStatus.name: repeaterSecurityPortAllStatus
repeaterSecurityPortAllStatus.description: Setting this field to invalid will delete all security addresses associated with this port. Setting this field to valid has no effect. If repeaterPortGroupIndex is equal to the group number of the agent, this object is read-write, otherwise it is read-only

repeaterSecurityPortSecurityLearn.name: repeaterSecurityPortSecurityLearn
repeaterSecurityPortSecurityLearn.description: Controls how the port will learn the destination addresses that can be sent to the port. If repeaterPortGroupIndex is equal to the group number of the agent, this object is read-write, otherwise it is read-only

repeaterSecurityTable.name: repeaterSecurityTable
repeaterSecurityTable.description: Table of security control for the ports.

repeaterSecurityEntry.name: repeaterSecurityEntry
repeaterSecurityEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing security information about a port.

repeaterSecurityGroupIndex.name: repeaterSecurityGroupIndex
repeaterSecurityGroupIndex.description: This variable identifies the group containing the security entry for which this entry contains information. The group ID may only be that of the target agent. Specifying a group ID of an agent in a different slot will result in `badValue` being returned.

repeaterSecurityPortIndex.name: repeaterSecurityPortIndex
repeaterSecurityPortIndex.description: This variable identifies the port containing the security entry for which this entry contains infromation.

repeaterSecurityAddress.name: repeaterSecurityAddress
repeaterSecurityAddress.description: This value will be compared to the destination address of all packets received on the port in applying the security action.

repeaterSecurityStatus.name: repeaterSecurityStatus
repeaterSecurityStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the rule.

repeaterSecurityAction.name: repeaterSecurityAction
repeaterSecurityAction.description: The action to take when the destination address matches.

repeaterSecurityGroupIndexShadow.name: repeaterSecurityGroupIndexShadow
repeaterSecurityGroupIndexShadow.description: This variable identifies the group containing a port to which a security address is to be assigned. The group ID may only be that of the target agent. Specifying a group ID of an agent in a different slot will result in `badValue` being returned.

repeaterSecurityPortIndexShadow.name: repeaterSecurityPortIndexShadow
repeaterSecurityPortIndexShadow.description: This variable identifies the port of a group to which a security address is to be assigned.

repeaterSecurityAddressShadow.name: repeaterSecurityAddressShadow
repeaterSecurityAddressShadow.description: This value contains the ethernet address which is to be added to the security address table for the port specified by repeaterSecurityGroupIndexShadow and repeaterSecurityPortIndexShadow.

repeaterSecurityStatusShadow.name: repeaterSecurityStatusShadow
repeaterSecurityStatusShadow.description: When read, this variable will always return 'ready'. When this variable is set to 'execute' the address specified by repeaterSecurityAddressShadow will be added to the security address table for the port specified by repeaterSecurityGroupIndexShadow and repeaterSecurityPortIndexShadow. If any of the above variables are zero when this object is set to 'execute', 'bad value' will be returned.

repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressTable.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressTable
repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressTable.description: Table of ethernet addresses which are applied globally (intra Network 9000 chassis) to ports.

repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressEntry.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressEntry
repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about a specific address.

repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressStatus.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressStatus
repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressStatus.description: This variable represents the status of the entry. Setting this object (or any other writable object) to 'valid' will cause the row in the table to be created. Setting this object to 'invalid' will cause the row to be removed.

repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressAction.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressAction
repeaterSecurityGlobalAddressAction.description: This variable determines the action which is applied to the packet in the event of an address match. The packet is either passed untouched when set to 'pass', or it is forced to an alternating pattern of ones and zeros if set to 'jam'.

repeaterSecurityGlobalDBID.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalDBID
repeaterSecurityGlobalDBID.description: This variable contains the current version number of the global security database.

repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityAdminState.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityAdminState
repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityAdminState.description: This variable controls whether global security is enabled or disabled. Global security will not function unless repeaterSecurityState and this variable are both set to `enabled`.

repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityOperState.name: repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityOperState
repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityOperState.description: This variable indicates the operational state of global security. If repeaterSecurityState is set to 'enabled' this variable will reflect the value of repeaterSecurityGlobalSecurityAdminState. if repeaterSecurityState is set to 'disabled', this variable will return 'securityDisabled'.

repeaterRepeaterTable.name: repeaterRepeaterTable
repeaterRepeaterTable.description: For repeaters that implement non-proxy management of logical repeaters, a table of descriptive and status information about a logical Ethernet repeater.

repeaterRepeaterEntry.name: repeaterRepeaterEntry
repeaterRepeaterEntry.description: An entry for a logical Ethernet repeater.

repeaterRepeaterIndex.name: repeaterRepeaterIndex
repeaterRepeaterIndex.description: The logical Ethernet repeater within the group.

repeaterRepeaterSegment.name: repeaterRepeaterSegment
repeaterRepeaterSegment.description: The Network 9000 Ethernet network segment to which the logical repeater is attached.

repeaterRepeaterReports.name: repeaterRepeaterReports
repeaterRepeaterReports.description: Control for whether statistical reports will be collected for this logical repeater.

repeaterRepeaterCollisions.name: repeaterRepeaterCollisions
repeaterRepeaterCollisions.description: The number of packet collisions detected on the Ethernet network segment to which this logical repeater is attached.

repeaterRepeaterJabbers.name: repeaterRepeaterJabbers
repeaterRepeaterJabbers.description: The number of Jabber events detected for this logical repeater.

repeaterRepeaterSQE.name: repeaterRepeaterSQE
repeaterRepeaterSQE.description: The number of SQE failure events detected for this logical repeater.

repeaterRepeaterFifoOverflows.name: repeaterRepeaterFifoOverflows
repeaterRepeaterFifoOverflows.description: The number of times the report FIFO was full when this logical repeater attemped to write a packet report.

repeaterRepeaterZero.name: repeaterRepeaterZero
repeaterRepeaterZero.description: Control for zeroing the logical repeater's counters. The agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting the value to 'execute' will zero the counters for the logical repeater.

repeaterRepeaterSinceZero.name: repeaterRepeaterSinceZero
repeaterRepeaterSinceZero.description: The number of hundredths of a second since the counters for this logical repeater were last zeroed. This variable is set to zero when repeaterRepeaterZero is written with the value 'execute'.

repeaterRepeaterSegmentsAllowed.name: repeaterRepeaterSegmentsAllowed
repeaterRepeaterSegmentsAllowed.description: The list of segments to which this repeater can be attached. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with a bit for 'none' and one bit for each segment, and enough octets for all the Ethernet segments in the chassis. The high order bit of the first octet corresponds to 'none', the following bits correspond to the segments, in order, beginning with A.

repeaterRepeaterTotalOctets.name: repeaterRepeaterTotalOctets
repeaterRepeaterTotalOctets.description: This variable will reflect the total number of bytes that the repeater both received from and sent to the segment. Bytes in both good and error frames are counted.

repeaterRepeaterTotalFrames.name: repeaterRepeaterTotalFrames
repeaterRepeaterTotalFrames.description: This variable will reflect the total number of frames that the repeater both received from and sent to the segment. Both good and error frames are counted.

repeaterRepeaterPercentUtilization.name: repeaterRepeaterPercentUtilization
repeaterRepeaterPercentUtilization.description: This variable will reflect the percentage of a full ethernet load that this repeater has handled since last zeroed. The value is calculated as `(8(totalBytes + (20*totalFrames)))/10 7(time)`.

repeaterRedundancyState.name: repeaterRedundancyState
repeaterRedundancyState.description: This variable controls whether hub redundancy is enabled

repeaterRedundancyGroupTable.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupTable
repeaterRedundancyGroupTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information concerning hub redundancy groups.

repeaterRedundancyGroupEntry.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupEntry
repeaterRedundancyGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about a specific hub redundancy group.

repeaterRedundancyGroupStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupStatus
repeaterRedundancyGroupStatus.description: This variable represents the status of the entry. Setting this object (or any other writable object) to 'valid' will cause the row in the table to be created. Setting this object to 'invalid' will cause the row to be removed. If a row is removed from the group table, all related rows in the path table and address table are also removed.

repeaterRedundancyGroupName.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupName
repeaterRedundancyGroupName.description: This variable represents the definable name of the group. Prior to being set, this object will return the default name 'Groupn' where n is the value of repeaterRedundancyGroupIndex. Setting this object to a zero length string will cause the default name to be assumed.

repeaterRedundancyGroupAdminState.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupAdminState
repeaterRedundancyGroupAdminState.description: This variable represents the desired state of the group. When this variable is set to 'enabled', the group will be activly monitored for integrity, and back- up paths will be brought up as higher priority paths disappear. When set to 'disabled', the path will not be tested for integrity.

repeaterRedundancyGroupTestInterval.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupTestInterval
repeaterRedundancyGroupTestInterval.description: This variable determines the rate at which testing is performed on the path which is currently active (repeaterRedundancyGroupOperPath) in order to determine integrity. The value is in milliseconds.

repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAdminStat.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAdminState
repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAdminStat.description: This variable represents the desired state of path rollback. Path rollback is defined as the automatic testing and reactivation of higher priority paths. It should be noted that in order to test higher priority paths, the currently enabled path will be interrupted. Setting this variable to 'enabled' will cause rollback testing to occur every repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackInterval number of milliseconds. Setting this variable to 'disabled' will force the group to remain on lower priority paths, until they themselves fail.

repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackInterval.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackInterval
repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackInterval.description: This variable determines the rate at which rollback testing is performed. The value is in milliseconds.

repeaterRedundancyGroupOperPath.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupOperPath
repeaterRedundancyGroupOperPath.description: This variable represents the index of the path which is currently being used as the active path. This value may be used as the value for repeaterRedundancyPathIndex to index the path table.

repeaterRedundancyGroupPathChanges.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupPathChanges
repeaterRedundancyGroupPathChanges.description: The value of this variable represents the number of times that this group has changed paths.

repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAttempts.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAttempts
repeaterRedundancyGroupRollbackAttempts.description: The value of this variable represents the number of times that the current path has been interrupted in interest of testing a higher priority path.

repeaterRedundancyGroupZero.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupZero
repeaterRedundancyGroupZero.description: This variable is used to zero all counters associated with a group. This variable when read will always read 'ready'. When set to 'execute', all counters associated with the group (group counters and path counters) will be set to zero.

repeaterRedundancyGroupSinceZero.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupSinceZero
repeaterRedundancyGroupSinceZero.description: The value of this variable represents the number of seconds which have elapsed since the counters associated with the group have been zeroed.

repeaterRedundancyGroupConfigStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyGroupConfigStatus
repeaterRedundancyGroupConfigStatus.description: In order for a particular redundancy group to be used by the system, it must have at least one redundancy path defined. This variable indicates whether a redundancy group has been completely configured, and can therefore become active.

repeaterRedundancyPathTable.name: repeaterRedundancyPathTable
repeaterRedundancyPathTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information concerning hub redundancy paths.

repeaterRedundancyPathEntry.name: repeaterRedundancyPathEntry
repeaterRedundancyPathEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about a specific hub redundancy path.

repeaterRedundancyPathPathIndex.name: repeaterRedundancyPathPathIndex
repeaterRedundancyPathPathIndex.description: This variable identifies the path of the group.

repeaterRedundancyPathStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyPathStatus
repeaterRedundancyPathStatus.description: This variable represents the status of the entry. Setting this object (or any other writable object) to 'valid' will cause the row in the table to be created. Setting this object to 'invalid' will cause the row to be removed. If a row is removed from the path table, all related rows in the address table are also removed.

repeaterRedundancyPathSlot.name: repeaterRedundancyPathSlot
repeaterRedundancyPathSlot.description: This variable represents the slot of the Network 9000 chassis which contains the repeater on which the path interface resides.

repeaterRedundancyPathPort.name: repeaterRedundancyPathPort
repeaterRedundancyPathPort.description: This variable represents the port of the repeater to which the path is connected.

repeaterRedundancyPathPriority.name: repeaterRedundancyPathPriority
repeaterRedundancyPathPriority.description: This variable represents the order of preferred priority for the path. Lower numbed paths are preferred over higher numbered paths.

repeaterRedundancyPathActivate.name: repeaterRedundancyPathActivate
repeaterRedundancyPathActivate.description: This variable is used to immediately make a specific path active. This variable when read will always read 'ready'. When set to 'execute', the selected path will become the active path for the group. Note that if rollback is enabled and this path is lower in priority, the system will attempt to restore the higher priority path.

repeaterRedundancyPathTimeout.name: repeaterRedundancyPathTimeout
repeaterRedundancyPathTimeout.description: This variable represents the amount of time in milliseconds that the syatem will wait for test responses from targets on the path.

repeaterRedundancyPathRetryCount.name: repeaterRedundancyPathRetryCount
repeaterRedundancyPathRetryCount.description: This variable represents the number of times a test is retried on the path in the event of a timeout before the path is considered useless.

repeaterRedundancyPathTestAttempts.name: repeaterRedundancyPathTestAttempts
repeaterRedundancyPathTestAttempts.description: The value of this variable represents the number of times that an integrity test was performed on the path.

repeaterRedundancyPathLastTestStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyPathLastTestStatus
repeaterRedundancyPathLastTestStatus.description: This variable indicates the result of the last test of the path. 'notTested' indicates that the path has yet to be tested. 'responded' indicates that a target on the path path has responded to the last test, 'timeout' indicates that no target on the path responded to the last test. 'integrity' indicates that a test was not performed on the path due to an abscense of port integrity.

repeaterRedundancyPathDisposition.name: repeaterRedundancyPathDisposition
repeaterRedundancyPathDisposition.description: This variable controls the action that will be taken when a path is considered bad. 'disable' indicates that the path is to be disabled prior to switching to an alternate path. 'null' indicates that the failed path is to be left in its current state prior to switching to an alternate path.

repeaterRedundancyPathConfigStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyPathConfigStatus
repeaterRedundancyPathConfigStatus.description: In order for a particular redundancy path to be used by the system, it must have at least one target address and the slot and the port on which it originates defined. This variable indicates whether a redundancy path has been completely configured, and can therefore become active.

repeaterRedundancyPathAdminState.name: repeaterRedundancyPathAdminState
repeaterRedundancyPathAdminState.description: This variable represents the desired state of the path. When this variable is set to 'disabled' the path will not be used by the group. When set to 'enabled', the path is available as an alternate or primary path.

repeaterRedundancyAddressTable.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressTable
repeaterRedundancyAddressTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information concerning hub redundancy target addresses.

repeaterRedundancyAddressEntry.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressEntry
repeaterRedundancyAddressEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about a specific target address associated with a hub redundancy path.

repeaterRedundancyAddressPathIndex.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressPathIndex
repeaterRedundancyAddressPathIndex.description: This variable identifies the path of the group.

repeaterRedundancyAddressAddress.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressAddress
repeaterRedundancyAddressAddress.description: This variable identifies the specific target address.

repeaterRedundancyAddressStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressStatus
repeaterRedundancyAddressStatus.description: This variable represents the status of the entry. Setting this object (or any other writable object) to 'valid' will cause the row in the table to be created. Setting this object to 'invalid' will cause the row to be removed.

repeaterRedundancyAddressResponses.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressResponses
repeaterRedundancyAddressResponses.description: This value of this variable represents the number of times this specific address has responded to a test attempt.

repeaterRedundancyAddressLastTestStatus.name: repeaterRedundancyAddressLastTestStatus
repeaterRedundancyAddressLastTestStatus.description: This variable indicates whether this particular address responded to the last test of the path. 'notTested' indicates that the path has yet to be tested. 'responded' indicates that the target responded to the last test, 'timeout' indicates that the target responded to the last test.

accessViolation.name: accessViolation
accessViolation.description: Access violation by connected system with Ethernet address not allowed by repeaterPortAccessTable and repeaterPortAccessAction.

integrityLoss.name: integrityLoss
integrityLoss.description: This port has lost link integrity.

redundancyPathChange.name: redundancyPathChange
redundancyPathChange.description: This trap issued to indicate that a redundancy group has experienced a path change. The offending group and the new path are included in the trap.
